# Task naming (agents + Linear)

**Bare IDs are forbidden in user-facing text.** `IPI-487` and `IPI-486` mean nothing without context.

## Required format

```text
{ID} · {SPEC} — {Plain English title}
```

| ✅ Good | ❌ Bad |
|---------|--------|
| **IPI-487 · CLOUDFLARE-EPIC — Cloudflare Platform Migration** | "the IPI-487 epic" |
| **CF-MIG-210 · Runtime Compatibility — Hono, OAuth & Groq Bundle** | "do 210 next" |
| **IPI-454 · CF-AI-001 — AI Gateway — Cloudflare Provider Routing** | "IPI-454 is blocked" |

## When writing

- **First mention** in a reply → full name (bold).
- **Roadmaps, tables, PR titles, commits** → full name every row/line.
- **Later in the same message** → plain English title only if still unambiguous (e.g. "Runtime Compatibility").
- **Links** → markdown link label uses full name; URL may use numeric ID.

## SSOT for canonical names

| Track | Lookup |
|-------|--------|
| Cloudflare migration | `tasks/cloudflare/todo.md`, `tasks/cloudflare/CLOUDFLARE-EPIC.md` |
| Mastra | `tasks/cloudflare/mastra/MASTRA-EPIC.md` |
| Any IPI task | Linear issue **title** or `docs/linear/issues/IPI-*.md` H1 |

If unsure of the title, read the SSOT or Linear before citing the ID.

## Linear issue titles

When creating or renaming issues, set **title** to the full format above (not `IPI-487` alone).
